c({"name": "funcunit.envjs", "type": "page", "comment": "<p>[http://www.envjs.com/ EnvJS] is a simulated browser environment. It can be used for running FuncUnit <br />\nunit tests. EnvJS can't be used for functional tests because it doesn't accurately implement event \nsimulation.</p>\n\n<h2>Use</h2>\n\n<p>There is no installation step for EnvJS. It comes with JavaScriptMVC.</p>\n\n<ol>\n<li>Write a unit test</li>\n<li>Run the test</li>\n</ol>\n\n<pre><code class='javascript'>test(\"unit test\", function(){\n  var a = new Animal();\n  a.setAge(2);\n  equals(a.getAge(), 2, \"age works\");\n})</code></pre>\n\n<pre><code class='javascript'>./js funcunit/open/envjs path/to/qunit.html</code></pre>\n\n<p>The same reporting system that is described in [funcunit.integrations Integrations] works with EnvJS.</p>", "title": "EnvJS", "parents": ["funcunit.integrations"], "order": 1, "src": "funcunit/pages/envjs.md", "children": []})